Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.96,0:00:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I suppose I should be happy that\NI'm back again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.27,0:00:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What isn't one thing that you got to be\Nhappy about? It's something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.68,0:00:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One damn happy thing after another.\NCan't even be miserable anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.92,0:00:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, "How can I get over being\Nmiserable?" I say, "Don't get over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.68,0:00:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be happy. Learn how to love being\Nmiserable."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.60,0:00:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of people do.\NOh, it's just horrible. Then you agree
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.84,0:01:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with them. You're right.\NYou're right. It is horrible. Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.04,0:01:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,all right. So, we we're talking about\Nthe roads to happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.84,0:01:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stop and examine yourself, you\Nbegin to wonder what are your goals?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.43,0:01:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you don't know what your goals\Nare, it's fun to just sit down and write
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.79,0:01:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,them down. Uh what are what are my goals\Nin this life? How many people here know
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.72,0:01:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what their goals are in this life? How\Nmany people have written them down?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.79,0:01:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Written them down. Oh boy. Oh boy.\NYeah. Just to make them more conscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.47,0:01:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you actually write them down. My goal in\Nthis life is boom. And uh then you can
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.32,0:01:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,prioritize them.\NUh of course, one good goal is to be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.79,0:02:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,happy no matter what happens.\NThen if you win, you say, "Hooray, I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.79,0:02:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,won." And then if you lose, you say,\N"Thank God I lost."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.31,0:02:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll come up with some of the reasons\Nfor that later in this list. That
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.80,0:02:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes is much better to lose.\NAnyway, being rich and famous seems to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.16,0:02:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,be an obsession with the television\Nindustry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.40,0:02:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, rich and famous is what they feed\Non. Rich and famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.31,0:02:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh,\Nso how to differentiate the flimsy ones
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.31,0:02:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,such as ri rich and famous from mature\Ngoals.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.31,0:02:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Be pleased with the direction you're\Ngoing instead of where you are with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.44,0:02:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Be pleased with the direction the your\Nalignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.76,0:03:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of saying I won't be happy\Nuntil I reach there or I won't be happy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.12,0:03:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,until I have $84,000 saved up, just be\Nhappy that you are in the direction of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.64,0:03:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to be thrifty and think about\Nyour older age and provide for whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.56,0:03:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So be happy that you are in a certain\Ndirection and of course spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.92,0:03:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that is very much so because there's\Nnowhere no way you can actually really
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.20,0:03:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,tell where you're at in your spiritual\Nevolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.12,0:03:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But to be happy with the fact that you\Nare your direction is to achieve
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.68,0:03:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment or salvation\Num to bring about good for others and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.00,0:03:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness to others. So be happy with\Nthe things that you have assigned a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.51,0:03:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,value to to be friendly and cheerful to\Nbe uplifting to others and I've always
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.15,0:03:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,tried to be uplifting to others. When\Nother people are depressed I clown
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.59,0:04:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,around them and get them to laugh and uh\Nmake life as easy as you can for other
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.87,0:04:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,people.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.36,0:04:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so be pleased with the direction that\Nyou have chosen for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.88,0:04:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the direction you're in and not how\Nfar you are along the path. The fact
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.24,0:04:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're on the path is what's\Nsignificant. How far you are of course
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.19,0:04:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is anybody's guess.\NSo we're talking about practical reality
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.63,0:04:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,versus fantasy. And of course we know\Nthat the these symbols of Hollywood
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.40,0:04:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,success and TV star success are you know\Nsymbolic
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.56,0:04:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and that it actually has to do with we\Nproject value onto it and that energy as
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.88,0:04:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,described by Alice Bailey is called\Nglamour. So it isn't that that person
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.04,0:05:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has has that. It's that you have\Nprojected desiraability
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.96,0:05:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,onto that.\NYou have projected desiraability onto
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.52,0:05:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that\Nin and of itself. It has no attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.19,0:05:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You say is that true? Yeah.\NNothing in this world has any attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.52,0:05:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you project attractiveness to it.\NIt's that uh attribute that that you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.03,0:05:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,have projected onto it that makes it\Ndesirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.12,0:05:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're like a dog chasing its tail.\NYou're like a dog. So most people in the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.56,0:05:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,world are like dogs chasing their tails.\NThey have decided that that is success.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.52,0:05:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My dog does it all the time. It's so\Nfunny. She starts to chase her tail. She
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.44,0:05:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,all a sudden you see her go. I said,\N"Why are you chasing your tail?" She
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.28,0:06:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,goes,\N"Kelsey, stop chasing your tail."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.12,0:06:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,For a minute, he she thought it was\Nsomething out there, but it's not out
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.56,0:06:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there. It's just It's just me I'm\Nchasing. Oh, it was more fun when I
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.36,0:06:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,thought it was something out there.\Nis not out there. It's in you. So
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,chasing your tail then is because you've\Nprojected wonderment down upon that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.40,0:06:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,thing is to pursue a thing because that\Nis what you are. If you're studious then
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.56,0:06:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,being a studious person uh is what you\Nare what you are. And um the thing is to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.72,0:06:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoy the process. Enjoy the process.\NEnjoy the process of life. Enjoy the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.91,0:06:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,various stages of life. It's fun to be a\Nkid. It's exciting to be an adolescent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:07:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's great to be a young adult.\NMiddle age has a lot of wonderful things
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.16,0:07:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,about it. Older age\Nuh is so is self-rewarding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.36,0:07:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too old to give a rap about it\Nanymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.44,0:07:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What other people worry about and die\Nfor. You say, "Yep, I remember when I
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.19,0:07:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,used to think that way." Yep. Yep.\NSo, you join the Yep. generation. Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.28,0:07:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a million bucks. Yep. I remember\Nwhen that was a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.36,0:07:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, in other words, what happening\Nis be is due to your own choice and your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.72,0:07:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,own decision. That puts you back in\Ncontrol. put you back in control to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.44,0:07:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that where you are is a result\Nof your own decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.24,0:07:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just an accident.\NYou choose and decide. You've chosen and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:08:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,decided uh to go in this direction.\NThat way you don't end up blaming it on
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.00,0:08:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,other people because no matter which way\Nyou go, there are risks involved. Is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.59,0:08:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that not so? Even if you decide to stay\Nhome and sit in your chair and not go
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.72,0:08:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere,\Nyou will then become decrepit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.87,0:08:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Decrepit. Right. All right. Move on to\Nthe next. We've got 101. We got to move
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.31,0:08:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,along.\NTo be flexible versus rigid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.63,0:08:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,To be flexible like the reed that bends\Nin the in the in the wind. the weed that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.03,0:08:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the the current so that the weed that\Nbends with the current uh is flexible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.24,0:08:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The one which is stiff and inflexible is\Nbroken by the current. So that's an old
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,tea teaist\Nuh teaching to be flexible and to bend
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:09:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with the wind and to bend with the bend\Nwith the current rather than break to be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.16,0:09:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,able to uh change to switch roles.\NYou can also see your life as a a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.04,0:09:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,sequence of roles.\NYou are not only what you are but you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.08,0:09:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,are fulfilling a certain social role.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.95,0:09:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the parent or the child or the those are\Nall rules
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.51,0:09:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and there and then we learn not to put\Nour happiness dependent on anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.24,0:09:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh you know I'll be happy if I get an A\Nin this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.12,0:09:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So you have to cancel and\Nthen I'll be happy and uh so that your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.92,0:09:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness is not provisional about\Nanything
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.39,0:09:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,except the direction that you're going.\NYou see I'm going in this direction. I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.04,0:09:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,choosing spiritual evolution as a\Nlifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.27,0:09:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand that it gives my life meaning and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:10:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,greater significance\Nand serving God in every way that I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.27,0:10:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,One way you serve God is by being happy.\NBeing God's will for you is happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.51,0:10:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore\Nuh to be happy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.39,0:10:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it's it's sort of just a style of\Nlanguaging is pleasing to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.64,0:10:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this go?\NSo God's demand
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.07,0:10:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you be happy.\NAnybody here refuse to be happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.27,0:10:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody wants to go to the lower places.\NSo being happy is fulfilling your human
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.83,0:10:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,potential.\NAnd uh we're we're created in that style
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.68,0:10:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,by almighty God.\NSo make the happiness independent of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.95,0:11:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,phenomena.\NTherefore, you don't have to clutch and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,grasp at things. clutching and grasping\Nat things then is a good way to lose
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,them.\NClarify your goals and your ideals. And
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.88,0:11:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm surprised how many people here\Nraised their hands that they have
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.16,0:11:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,actually sat down and listed what their\Ngoals are and prioritized them. And of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.20,0:11:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,course in act in actual life we're doing\Nthat all the time but it's unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.68,0:11:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We're choosing and choosing one goal\Nover another uh constantly. But to make
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.48,0:11:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,them conscious, intellectually aware is\Nof great value.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.24,0:11:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that all value that you\Nattribute to anything is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.60,0:11:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, because you value it doesn't\Nmean that it is. It just means that you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.12,0:11:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,value it. The only value that I would\Nsay is independent of personal opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.76,0:12:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is the scale of consciousness. The scale\Nof consciousness indicates
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.68,0:12:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh on a mathematical arithmetic level\Nuh value when looked at from the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.44,0:12:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,viewpoint of consciousness itself. But\Nmany people would disregard that as of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.68,0:12:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,any value. So even that which is a\Nconfirmatory value would not be valuable
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.04,0:12:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in another person's eyes. Honesty,\Nintegrity, honesty and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.88,0:12:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in our culture, honesty and\Nintegrity are virtues. There are other
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.95,0:12:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,cultures in which honesty and integrity\Nis idiotic and stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.51,0:12:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side of the world,\Nif the price of this subject is $6 and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.39,0:12:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and you sell it for $6, they can say\Nyou're an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.63,0:12:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Honesty, integrity in a different\Nculture
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.95,0:13:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is considered\Nstupidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.95,0:13:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how do you accommodate yourself to\Na culture that thinks the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.12,0:13:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,honesty, etc.\Nis a defect?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.04,0:13:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little hard to figure how you're\Ngoing to accommodate
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.39,0:13:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to something that is diametrically\Nopposed to your own set of values.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.07,0:13:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,clarify goals and ideals. Realize that\Nall value is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.12,0:13:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There are huge cultures in which\Nuh honesty is considered stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.83,0:13:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Honesty is stupidity.\NYes. Happiness is a a nap on a train or
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.27,0:13:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a plane. No,\NI just thought I'd put some quickies in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.60,0:14:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\NYou put up your feet and have a quick
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.24,0:14:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,nap and you're happy no matter where you\Nare. Okay, there. Okay. Right. We got uh
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.56,0:14:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,101 to go. We better move along.\NLive one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.72,0:14:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the 12step The 12step program is one\Nof the greatest sources of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.04,0:14:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,People who practice the 12step program\Nare happier than other people. And you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.51,0:14:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,can even calibrate them that they are\Nactually happier. They actually live in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.72,0:14:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the five in the 500s.\NAnd one of the axioms is to live one day
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.51,0:14:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time. Uh is that rational? Well,\Nyesterday is gone forever. That has so
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.19,0:14:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it has no reality. Uh tomorrow isn't\Nhere yet. So it has no reality. So the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.36,0:14:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,only thing that's really real is what's\Nright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.95,0:14:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So living one day at a time is a very\Nimportant part of the 12step program. So
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.19,0:15:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,12step program calibrates around 570 and\Nit's higher than any other uh pathway uh
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.12,0:15:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,currently available.\NUh so be be lucky if you're lucky if you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.88,0:15:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,have something that requires you to go\Nto and join a 12step program.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.88,0:15:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you haven't got a problem, you better\Ngo get one so you can go
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.51,0:15:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can live one one day at a time.\NNo matter what comes up, I say, "Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.00,0:15:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that was yesterday." And yesterday, I\Nthought, "What'll I talk about tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.36,0:15:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,at the lecture?" And I said, "Well, I'll\Nworry about that tomorrow when tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.63,0:15:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,gets here."\NHappiness is a cat's purr or a dog's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.83,0:15:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,wagging tail. We calibrated them at 500\Nand something. A cat's purr. It's hard
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.36,0:15:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to be angry, upset, and self-pity when a\Nkitty's bringing your arm. You got this
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.19,0:15:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,kitty and she's going,\N"I have a cat home. I paid 50 bucks for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.68,0:16:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,this cat. It's my $50 cat\Nnamed Bootsie. So, matter no matter what
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.63,0:16:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I do, Bootsie wants to participate."\NWell, I have to do the checkbook,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.12,0:16:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,balance the checkbook at home, and he\Nloves the checkbook. The minute I get it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.12,0:16:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,out,\Nhe claims the checkbook to be his.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.27,0:16:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to feel unhappy, I said, "Give\Nme back my checkbook."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is a cat's purr. There's\Nnothing nicer than hearing kitties
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.60,0:16:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,purring. And sometimes I come home and\Nthere's all three kitties sitting
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.44,0:16:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,around. All three of them are purring.\NPurr
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.56,0:16:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,like you. All three of them purring. And\Nthe three of them are there purring. In
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.88,0:16:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the meantime, down the kitchen floor,\Nthe dog's tail is wagging.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.75,0:16:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's very hard to be unhappy.\NThree pitties purring at once and the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.39,0:16:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,dog wagging his tail. The only thing\Nthat make you happy is your wife's voice
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.95,0:17:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,comes over and says, "Dinner's ready.\NNow you got the ultimate happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.40,0:17:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinner is ready, the cats are purring,\Nand the dog's tail is wagging. Who could
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.67,0:17:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,want for anything more, right?\NAnother source of happiness is faith
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.88,0:17:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,versus skepticism.\NThe skeptic uh skepticism is a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.64,0:17:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,narcissistic position\Nand uh faith is a much higher position.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.08,0:17:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So faith, of course, the person who's a\Nskeptic at the same time idiotically
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.52,0:17:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't realize it isn't his skepticism.\NIt's his faith in his skepticism that's
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.88,0:17:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping him alive.\NHe thinks skepticism will lead me to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.00,0:17:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,truth and happiness and and that's why\Nhe's a skeptic. But it's his faith and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.96,0:17:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,his skepticism that gives him that\Nfeeling. Isn't that paradoxically funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.20,0:18:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you was skeptical about a\Nskeptic skepticism, you'd be making
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.44,0:18:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,progress.\NI don't think too much of skepticism is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.28,0:18:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the road to happiness.\NI'm skeptical about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.76,0:18:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have faith that my skepticism of\Nwhat is skepticism will lead me to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.44,0:18:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness.\NAll right? So we learn to be grateful
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.28,0:18:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for what we what we ha have and what we\Nhave become.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.24,0:18:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Grateful for what we have and for what\Nwe have become. You know people say are
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.36,0:18:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you grateful that you're older and I say\Nwell considering the alternative. Very
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.55,0:18:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,good indeed.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.91,0:18:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Maurice shio gratitude for what one has\Nand what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.12,0:18:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what we've learned as is a result of all\Nthe effort we put in. We've traveled all
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.08,0:19:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,those miles through life to become what\Nwe are at this moment. So we're the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.84,0:19:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,product of the past.\NSo we're we can build upon the past and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.20,0:19:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we're also attracted by the future. So\Nhere we are in no man's land between the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.16,0:19:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,past which is over and the future which\Nisn't here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.55,0:19:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see? You live in a complete\Nvacuum. The past is over. The future
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.72,0:19:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't here yet. Though the only place\Nyou can exist is in this present moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.12,0:19:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only thing you have to worry\Nabout is this present moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.60,0:19:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This present moment.\NDetached versus craving means if it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.55,0:19:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,happens, it's terrific. And if it\Ndoesn't, it's okay. The capacity to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.91,0:20:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,become detached is a learned is a\Nlearned uh technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.55,0:20:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody should find practice becoming\Ndetached from something you think you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.28,0:20:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,just have to have to be happy. Pick\Nsomething arbitrarily
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.72,0:20:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and start becoming detached from it. You\Nsay, "Well, if I become detached from
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.00,0:20:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it, then I won't get it, will I?\NSo the prison wants to become detached
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.03,0:20:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and still be attached.\NThat's a sneaky trick and I won't let
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.52,0:20:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you get away with it.\NDetached means if it happens, great. And
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.20,0:20:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,if it doesn't happen, fine.\NOne way or the other, it's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.79,0:20:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because that which I am in reality\Nis not going to be affected one way or
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.20,0:20:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the other. I've either learned how to\Nderive happiness from my own existence
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.40,0:20:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or I haven't. And if I haven't learned\Nhow to derive happiness from my own
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.60,0:20:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,existence, then what could possibly make\Nme happier?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.32,0:21:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can't be happy worth this much, how\Nwill I be happier if I'm worth twice as
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.55,0:21:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,much?\NSo, gratitude for what one has and is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.03,0:21:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have become. Anybody sitting in\Nthis audience is obviously in a good
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.79,0:21:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,place. They should be grateful for what\Nwhat what they have become because the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.36,0:21:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,searching after truth and all of its\Nexpressions is one of the most advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.15,0:21:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,states of consciousness there is. To\Nseek truth for its own sake and to go
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.67,0:21:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,wherever one has to go to learn truth is\Ntherefore a great goal. gratitude that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.28,0:21:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you're even interested in in integrity\Nand truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.60,0:21:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that about 98% of the world\Nis not interested in in in truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.03,0:21:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,One time we did on the arm on that the\Nnumber of people who are interested in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.64,0:22:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment if you stop them on the\Nstreet is less than one in 10 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.52,0:22:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stop everybody on the street,\Nafter 10 million people, you'll find one
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.36,0:22:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,person. My ultimate goal in this\Nlifetime is enlightenment. Let's see if
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.88,0:22:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that's changed. That's still the same.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.67,0:22:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The chances of even\Ndesiring enlightenment are one in 10
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.55,0:22:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,million on the street. The Buddha said,\Nyou know, rare rare it is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.15,0:22:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,great great good karma to have heard\Nheard of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.64,0:22:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The first great good karma is that you\Nhave heard of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.72,0:22:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The second is that you decide to pursue\Nit. The having heard of it, you decide
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.32,0:23:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to pursue it. And rarest of all is to\Npursue it and achieve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.48,0:23:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Buddha said that therefore that\Nyou in this audience are rare indeed and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.76,0:23:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in good karma. Everybody in this\Naudience has good karma. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.03,0:23:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOh, happy happy Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.20,0:23:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha says, "My God, they heard me."\NOh,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.88,0:23:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,fortunate is the Buddha who has\Nfollowers to listen to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.79,0:23:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that like it's the Buddha that's\Nhappy? That Buddha that's lucky. How
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.24,0:23:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,many Buddhas have people who pay any\Nattention to him? That's what I always
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.08,0:24:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,say.\NYeah, I like the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.79,0:24:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratitude for what one has and is\Ndetachment versus craving. So to become
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.08,0:24:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment, the enlightenment is the\Nreleasing of attachments and aversions
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.24,0:24:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore of cravings. So the\Nenttrapment into the body which
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.91,0:24:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,initiates through the senses in the\Nbeginning
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.64,0:24:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the enlightenment means becoming\Ndetached to letting go craving to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.91,0:24:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go. If it happens it happens and\NI will enjoy it and if it doesn't then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.55,0:24:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be doing something else.\NIf I'm not doing this this morning then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.03,0:24:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I would be doing something else this\Nmorning. Isn't that so? I could be home
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.48,0:24:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kitties could be purring and the\Ndog wagging his tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.00,0:24:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Detached versus craving.\NCraving is always putting a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.12,0:25:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,desiringness. Craving is always\Na wanting something that you have
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.27,0:25:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,glamorized and said that will make me\Nhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.00,0:25:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole attitude of of life is is the\Nglass half full or is it half empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.55,0:25:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Optimism or pessimism?\NOptimism and pessimism.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.36,0:25:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the glass half full or half empty? So\Nthere we're saying how your perception
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.20,0:25:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of life, how you contextualize it. Is it\Nhalf full or half empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.55,0:26:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NIt's half full because it's half empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.91,0:26:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it both ways.\NFirst time in history anybody won that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.67,0:26:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,one conundrum.\NIt's half full because it's half empty,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.15,0:26:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,idiot.\NIt's half to empty because it's half
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.76,0:26:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,full. Isn't that easy?\NTook me to come along and solve that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.08,0:26:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,conundrum.\NI don't know how the world survived
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.12,0:26:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,without it.\NDetach means if I find the answer to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.88,0:26:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,something that's terrific and I have to\Nlet go of the craving the craving
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.32,0:26:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh for knowing the answer. When you\Nstart getting investigating researching
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.88,0:26:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,truth and its various expressions\Nuh this can befall you where you begin
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.20,0:26:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to\Nuh you get you have to know the answer
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.44,0:27:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to this one\Nand you drive your spouse crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.32,0:27:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in the morning. I'll come in the other\Nand she'll she can tell I'm coming. I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.24,0:27:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Honey, could I have your arm? One\Nsecond.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.96,0:27:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I just have to know what such and such\Ncalibrates that. I just have to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.88,0:27:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know. I just have to know." And of\Ncourse, I don't have to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.64,0:27:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, I realize it's not a have\Nto, it's a want to. want to intellectual
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.08,0:27:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,curiosity of course intellectual\Ncuriosity what is what drove the whole
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.15,0:27:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,renaissance the great books of the\Nwestern world so a great deal of wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.44,0:27:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of that\Nuh is sort of a positive curiosity
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.27,0:27:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,optimist thinks that increasing one's\Nconsciousness level will increase one's
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.39,0:27:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness\Nand that's optimistic and it's also
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.96,0:28:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfillable\NAnd in order to do that, we choose
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.91,0:28:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual versus material goals. Why?\NBecause spiritual goals are
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.96,0:28:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,uh cannot be lost. Spiritual goals are\Nvaluable beyond all time and beyond the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.36,0:28:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,physical. Material goals come and go.\NThe morning you get up and you turn on
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.55,0:28:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the Rasmusen report or what is that one?\Nsomething report tells you what where
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.55,0:28:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you lost money yesterday.\NWell, yesterday it had all these famous
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.91,0:28:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,people that are multi-millionaires\Nand how much they lost. They all lost
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.08,0:28:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,25% of their money and anyway that won't\Naffect their happiness because the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.67,0:28:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity to make more money is there.\NSo, it's the capacity then the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.44,0:28:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the thing itself.\Nspiritual versus material goals. Now
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.84,0:29:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the things of the world, the\Nthings that we uh surrender to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.67,0:29:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are the things that we\Nsurrender to God. Surrender those things
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.03,0:29:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world to mammon and that which is\Nof spiritual to God and not confuse the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.32,0:29:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,two. Surrender that which is God's to\NGod and that which is material to man.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.44,0:29:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible says. Okay. Next thing,\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.91,0:29:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the surrendering to God's will is a\Nsophisticated
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.48,0:29:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding\Nthat really evolves
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.76,0:29:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with your own level of consciousness. As\Nyour own level of consciousness evolves,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.91,0:29:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the understanding of God's will\Nbecomes progressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.03,0:29:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and can't really be described verbatim\Nas it progresses. And the when you're a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.72,0:30:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,kid, you think God's will is that you go\Nto church
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.64,0:30:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,uh you don't use certain bad words and\Nvarious things. So God your
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.84,0:30:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of what is God's will\Nevolves uh over the decades and finally
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.79,0:30:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes almost inex you can't really\Nexplain it. It's more contextualized, a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.20,0:30:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualized knowingness,\Na knowingness that at this moment, in
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.39,0:30:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,this instant, in this evolution,\Nthat this is the way to go rather than
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.03,0:30:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this way. So a certain knowingness\Nevolves and we call it wisdom spir a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.76,0:30:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,certain spiritual wisdom to surrender to\NGod's will then
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.96,0:30:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,brings about an evolution of one's\Nwisdom. Is it God's will that I take up
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.32,0:30:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,arms and fight or is it God's will that\NI surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.60,0:31:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,whether to take up arms against the\Nslings and arrows of outrageous fortune
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.96,0:31:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or\Nbattle them. So this is really a a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.88,0:31:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,conflict of not a conflict but a\Nconundrum
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.03,0:31:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which is permanent\Nand all the evolutionary phases of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.32,0:31:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean to surrender to God's\Nwill at that point? For some people to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.91,0:31:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender to God's will means to obey\Nthe command and shoot the enemy. For
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.24,0:31:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,another person to surrender to God's\Nwill means I cannot kill another human
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.03,0:31:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,under any circumstance.\NSo what is God's will?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.76,0:31:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're 18 and you're in the Navy and\Nthey say shoot him, God's will is that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.12,0:31:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you shoot him.\NIf you're 82 and they say shoot him, you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.88,0:31:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,say I'm not going to shoot him.\NSo what is God's will?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.96,0:32:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Means\Nfor you at this time in this context. So
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.24,0:32:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,truth cannot be you know defined\Nunless you define it within the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.64,0:32:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In what circumstances\Nis it evil to do this or not to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.00,0:32:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to uh retrospectively make things that\Nwere done under threat of war illegal is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.48,0:32:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,like an outrage to\Nuh this violation of God's will because
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.88,0:32:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the cir what's truth and what's God's\Nwill
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.51,0:32:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,truth is dependent on circumstance on\Ncontext what's true in this context is a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.84,0:32:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,lie in this context what's dutiful and\Nfulfilling your obligation to mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.27,0:32:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and about here is a violation of it\Nthere. Yes. So this is this is where
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.15,0:32:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual evolution leads to progressive\Nsophistication.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.20,0:33:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What is God's will for you at this\Nmoment in these circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.24,0:33:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were older then it would be\Ndifferent. If you were younger it would
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.76,0:33:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,be different. But you're not older and\Nyou're not younger. You're who you are
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.84,0:33:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,right at this moment. So for you at this\Nmoment, what is the highest thing that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.84,0:33:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do? Serve your country or become\Na conscientious objector?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.03,0:33:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I practiced psychiatry many\Nyears, 50 years, and I forget what war
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.51,0:33:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it was, Vietnam, I guess. Lots of people\Nwanted to could had to be seen by me and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.91,0:33:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,uh whether they were capable, etc. And\Nthe question I always was run up against
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.64,0:33:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was\Nuh if if you don't want to go to Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.72,0:33:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and kill anybody, I'd say, well, you can\Nyou got two options. You can move to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.60,0:33:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Canada or you can just become a\Nconscientious objector. Just be a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.91,0:34:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,conscientious objector. And that solved\Nit. So you don't have to be anti
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.84,0:34:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,something. You can find a livable\Nuh space in which you can live. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.96,0:34:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,serve your country and be a\Nconscientious objector
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.04,0:34:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can work in the stock room. You\Ndon't have to shoot people if you really
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.20,0:34:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,can't shoot people. So right now I'd say\Nno, I can't shoot people now. It's just
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.52,0:34:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,don't work out for me.\NCan't stand all the noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.59,0:34:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll lead a prayer group in the back\Nwhile you folks go ahead do the shooting
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.91,0:34:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,part. When you're done shooting, let me\Nknow.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.07,0:34:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to let go then is freedom.\NCapacity to surrender to God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.83,0:34:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,increases the capacity to let go. To let\Ngo is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.83,0:34:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,be progressively more and more easy. Can\Nyou let go of anything? Eventually you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.88,0:35:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,reach the point where you can really let\Ngo of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.40,0:35:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean let go seriously.\NYou can overlook things, you can skip
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.04,0:35:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,things. But a very serious let go of\Nmeaning really let go becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.40,0:35:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively easier.\NUh which is uh very nice that it is that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.11,0:35:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,way. Uh surrender to God's will then is\Nthe capacity to let go. And when we we
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.64,0:35:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nis we surrender our our love ourself to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.88,0:35:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,God out of love for God. And therefore\Nthe capacity to let go is almost
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.07,0:35:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite.\NIf people say I can't think do a thing I
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.64,0:35:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,say you can't let go of it. I said now\Nif I hold the gun to your head and if
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.80,0:35:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't let go I'm going to blow your\Nbrains out. Suddenly they can let go. So
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.56,0:36:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand letting go. Anything you\Nthink you're caught with and you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.16,0:36:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of it.\NYou picture a gun at your head and ask
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.28,0:36:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself now, can you let go of it?\NAnybody stuck on something they can't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.24,0:36:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of?\NHoney, did I bring the gun this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.72,0:36:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or not?\NIf we hold a gun to your head, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.07,0:36:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,amazing. You can let go of anything.\NAll right. So, you be pleased with your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.48,0:36:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,own progress. The capacity to let go is\Nthere. It isn't can you, it's will you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.59,0:36:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's a matter of the human will. You\Nsay I can't let go of it. The minute you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.59,0:36:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,hear yourself saying, "I can't let go of\Nthat." Tell yourself the truth is I
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.16,0:36:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,won't let go of it. Okay? You won't let\Ngo of it. That puts it in a different
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.80,0:36:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,domain because something you can't let\Ngo of today, you may be able to a week
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.52,0:37:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,from now, a year from now, or a decade\Ndecade from now, it's easy to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.48,0:37:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, being a movie star is hard to\Nlet go of as a adolescent fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.40,0:37:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But by 80, you've gotten over it.\NSo, I'm pleased with my progress. I
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.96,0:37:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to want to be Clark Gable\Nanymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.40,0:37:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Clark Gable was our hero when I grew up.\NYou know, Clark Gable, if you could only
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.92,0:37:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,be Clark Gable.\NSo, you don't have to be Clark Gable now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.72,0:37:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to be happy. And you avoid self-\Njudgment. Now, we said the self-
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.11,0:37:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,judgment is in the internalized parent.\NSee, there's the child in you. There's
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.56,0:37:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the adult and then judgmentalism is the\Ninner parent. The supereid super ego is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.56,0:37:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly judging everything you do.\NHow to handle that inner judge all the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.48,0:38:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,time. Uh so the child if you want to\Nenjoy life the child has to stay alive
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.20,0:38:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to\Nhave a child that's handy. Child come
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.48,0:38:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,here.\NI have to sit on my child all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.00,0:38:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Very observous. Wants to take over\Neverything.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.48,0:38:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not going to take you seriously\Nif you're so childish. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.52,0:38:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. Yes. I must be serious\Nand dignified.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.92,0:38:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope.\NI did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.83,0:38:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That takes care of the kids.\NHaving your inner kid alive and well is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.40,0:38:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,part of happiness.\NSo that you can sit on the kid
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.88,0:39:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,periodically\Nwhen he's in the street car or
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.16,0:39:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,something. I used to go with my younger\Nsister and I'd have to be with her on
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.52,0:39:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the street car. I was like 10 or 11 and\Nshe was like seven or something. So she
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.07,0:39:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Now you sit next to your brother."\NSo she'd be very good and we get on the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.56,0:39:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,street car and we s she'd be sitting\Nnext to me and next thing you know she
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.04,0:39:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,start wandering down the aisle of the\Nstreet car and she's running up and down
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.04,0:39:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the aisle laughing and giggling and\Nrunning up and down and I pretend I
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.11,0:39:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't know her.\NI would shrink down with shame and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.07,0:39:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,embarrassment.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.80,0:39:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So she was being bad and uh\NI was being good.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.32,0:40:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So to me, being good was the way to\Nhappiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.88,0:40:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And for her, doing what the hell she\Nwanted was her way to happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.20,0:40:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm going to meet. See, I can't wait\Nto see my sister again on the other
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.80,0:40:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,side. She was adorable. Just loved her\Nto pieces. But she loved being bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.68,0:40:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was it bad? because it was on the\Nstreet car and my mother said you're
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.16,0:40:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,supposed to sit in your seats and not\Nrun up and down the aisle in the street
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.24,0:40:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,car. Okay. So the circumstances\Nmade it good or bad. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.20,0:40:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore our human values to win is\Nprovisional. What do you mean by win?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.59,0:40:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know many time we see people seing\Nsomething that to them is a win and we
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.80,0:40:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,see it as a as a loss or vice versa. So\Nwhat is a win is how you define it. How
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.83,0:41:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you contextualize it.\NWhether it's a win or a loss is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.56,0:41:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,dependent upon the circumstances.\NSimplicity versus complexity. That which
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.96,0:41:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is really super complex is harder to\Nachieve than that which is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.52,0:41:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, one way to make life\Nbehave better is to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.64,0:41:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,take something that is staggeringly\Ncomplex and boil it down to its inner
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.56,0:41:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,inner principles.\NSimplicity out of complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.83,0:41:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If a thing is too complex, it just can't\Nbe handled and it gets discarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.96,0:41:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Discarded\Nlike college algebra.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.31,0:41:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,good friend of mine is struggling\Nthrough college algebra and Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.88,0:41:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,God. Jesus. Your karma. Well,\Nyou know, struggling through college
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.52,0:41:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,algebra. I got to say that is really\Nmaybe one of the maximum
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.00,0:42:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh things you got to live through. But\Nit's sort of a right of passage. It
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.28,0:42:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't until you complete all these\Nalgebra courses you realize that they're
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.80,0:42:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,totally useless.\NThere isn't any good to know that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.56,0:42:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,algebra can serve you in today's life.\NYou got a computer that'll do it that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.31,0:42:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,fast. You haven't even written it down\Nto start figuring it out. The computer's
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.00,0:42:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,got it already.\NWhat are you going to do with college
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.16,0:42:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,algebra?\NWell, it's a right of passage. It's a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.56,0:42:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,right of passage.\NYou just can't get there without doing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.48,0:42:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,college algebra.\NAnd instantly you get sympathy from
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.20,0:42:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody. Say, "What are you doing\Ntonight?" He said, "I'm studying college
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.28,0:42:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,algebra." And you all go, "Oh jeez,\Nlet me give you a piece of pie to take
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.28,0:42:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,home something to make\Nmake up for having to study college
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.44,0:43:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,algebra all night. It's a right of\Npassage." And of course, it's outlive
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.31,0:43:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,its usefulness. Any computer can do it\Nin a 1,000th of a second. what takes you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.83,0:43:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,all evening computer can do in no time\Nat all. So life moves on uh from
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.59,0:43:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,complexity simplicity. So that which was\Nundoable through complexity is now
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.56,0:43:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,doable through simplicity.\NSo we try to simplify life's problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.44,0:43:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's move on to the next\Nuh realistic expectations of life and of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.28,0:43:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,others and of events. What can you\Nrealistically expect of certain things?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.40,0:43:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're going to be interested in\Npolitics, you've got to modify your
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.83,0:43:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,expectations. If you expect honesty and\Nintegrity and all that, forget it. Just
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.11,0:43:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,get realistic. You're in a different\Nworld with different values. Now, the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.16,0:43:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,thing is, you cannot judge their world\Nby your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.52,0:44:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've had to struggle through that\Nmyself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.44,0:44:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Their world is not your world.\NIn their world, making it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.40,0:44:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it takes a few bucks here and a\Nfew bucks there and lying here and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.24,0:44:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,testifying falsely, that's what their\Ngame is about. You can't use your rules
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.76,0:44:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and put it in their domain because in\Ntheir domain you would be an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.28,0:44:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nwhat you values then are contextual
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.88,0:44:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,depend on who you are where you are in\Nlife and therefore we can't judge
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.59,0:44:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,others.\NValue is in the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.88,0:44:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What you think is valuable is what's\Nvaluable.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.11,0:44:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to give up your skepticism.\NAs we said, you know, you can be
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.16,0:44:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,skeptical about anything except you're\Nskeptical. Your skepticism in sense and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.59,0:45:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a sense of humor serves you in all of\Nthese 101 ways
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.59,0:45:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to be happy. All of them\Nis are enhanced by a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.31,0:45:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of humor\Nexcept karmic propensity. Many things
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.83,0:45:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,are karmic.\NThis means a propensity, a tendency.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.76,0:45:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not cause and effect, but a\Nlikelihood. And when we investigated it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.40,0:45:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with consciousness research,\Nthere is a high likelihood if you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.92,0:45:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of negative karma. It isn't that the\Nnegative karma causes the earthquake to
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.28,0:45:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,handle happen just where you live. But\Nbecause you have that karma, you happen
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.00,0:45:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to be there. So it's a propensity, not a\Ncausality.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.83,0:45:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma doesn't cause anything, but the\Nlikelihood of certain things happen is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.88,0:45:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly being enhanced.\NSee essence rather than perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.59,0:46:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's that was the wolf and sheep's\Nclothing. Be jocular instead of morose.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.20,0:46:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jocular instead of morose.\NWhat's 41?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.28,0:46:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,reg good will regarding all of life. And\Nthis is the one that pays off the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.16,0:46:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodwill regarding all of life makes all\Nof the rest of these easier. All you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.52,0:46:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,need is that one and a hundred other\Nways to be happy uh come about.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.76,0:46:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody's ate you ate your hamburger\Nwhen you went to the man's room, you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.56,0:46:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Well,\NI guess he was hungry and didn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.40,0:46:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,any money." Goodw will regarding all of\Nlife makes all of them easier. To be
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.20,0:47:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,easygoing, uh uplifting, easygoing\Nversus rigid and re you can do that by
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.96,0:47:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,reducing expectations of others.\NIf you don't expect anything of them at
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.24,0:47:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,all, you're never disappointed.\NIf somebody's integrous, honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.56,0:47:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,intelligent, and educated, I fall over.\NOh,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.64,0:47:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,reduce your expectations of others. And\NI've mentioned before that if you have
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.40,0:47:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,good will towards all of life, you'll\Nsee what an what a an effect you have on
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.04,0:47:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,people. And I always say when you're in\Na store and they ring you up on the cash
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.76,0:47:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,register, you you thank them very much.\NYou say, "Thank you a lot for racking
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.72,0:47:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that all up." And they'll go, "Huh?"\NThey do it hundreds of times before
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.72,0:47:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody says, "Thank you for ringing\Nthat up." Reduce your expectations of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.52,0:47:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,others. Be generous instead of stingy.\NGenerous with what? generous with
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.00,0:48:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself,\Nnot generous with one thing or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.20,0:48:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Generosity is an attitude towards life,\Na givingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.80,0:48:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,uh a nurturance.\NYou're generous towards all of life. You
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.35,0:48:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,walk through the woods and you say, "My\NGod, these trees are magnificent and
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.00,0:48:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful."\NNow, I love the trees in the woods. I
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.31,0:48:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,adore them. Now, let's see. Our person\Nasks, "The trees in the woods are know
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.76,0:48:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm glad and love them.\NThe trees in the woods know that you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.07,0:48:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,love them. All of life bows down before\Nthat which is loving and reflects the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.48,0:48:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,div God's love." Okay. The woods, the\Ntrees are literally aware of your
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.11,0:48:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingness of them. Resist\Nall of life then responds to what you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.48,0:49:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,not what you have not what you do not\Nwhat you say but what you have become
